<TITLE> ECNEC approves Ctg flyover </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jun 01 (bdnews24.com)  The Executive Committee of the National Economic Council Tuesday approved six projects worth Tk 13.3 billion, including construction of a flyover in Chittagong and the amended housing project. They were approved in an ECNEC meeting, presided over by prime minister Sheikh Hasina, at Sher-e-Bangla Nagar's NEC auditorium, planning minister AK Khandker told journalists while elaborating upon the projects. He also said that the government will be funding the projects. The flyover to be built at Chittagong's Muradpur within June 2012 by the housing and public works ministry was estimated to cost around Tk 1.5 billion, Khandker said. Khandker said that the housing project (phase-2, 3rd amendment), which is already being implemented by the prime minister's office, was allocated approximately Tk 6 billion. A total of 65,000 homeless and landless people would be rehabilitated and trained under the project spanning from July 2002 to Dec 2010. The water ministry's project of constructing an additional pump station in Goranchanbari for Tk 800 million, local government division's Tk 1.79 billion 'Greater Comilla Village Structure Development project', health ministry's Tk 1.38 billion project for establishment of a national institute of laboratory medicine and referral centre and the power division's Tk 17.3 billion 'Renovation and Augmentation of Distribution Lines and 11/0.4 Kv Sub-Stations under Six Distribution Zones of BPDP Project' also received approval. bdne
